+\subsection{Item~1 --- M4 V0 closure (deg-$a=0$ row mechanism)}
+\label{sec:closure-cascade-m4}
+
+The M4 stratum closure landed on the bridge as
+\texttt{M4-V0-CLOSURE-CASCADE-106} (bridge SHA \texttt{5f9db69},
+2026-05-08). The canonical synth-ratified closure statement (Claude
+Opus 4.7, T1-Synth, Claude.ai web; \verb|ACCEPT_W_REVISIONS|) reads
+in part:
+\emph{``M4 V0 CLOSED via the deg-$a=0$ row mechanism (068 verdict
+\textsf{UPGRADE\_FULL\_VIA\_DEG\_A\_ZERO\_ROW}). The deg-$a=0$ row
+supersedes the prior expected closure path
+(Costin--Borderline / Birkhoff--Trjitzinsky 1933 \S 1 anormal
+$q=2$ fractional-rank resurgence) and provides the structural
+M4-stratum closure at zero acquisition cost. The closure runs at the
+algebraic-combinatorial level via the four-row Phase A WZ-balance
+enumeration extension and the V6 closed-form general formula
+$A_{\mathrm{naive}} = 2d - d_a$, specialised to $d_a = 0$ to give
+$A_{\mathrm{naive}} = 2d$ uniformly at general $d \geq 2$.''}
+Confidence is recorded as \emph{MEDIUM-HIGH; HIGH-pending} on
+post-W21-LANE-1 ratification + post-Wasow \S X.3 OCR acquisition.
+Numerical residuals at the original 068 dispatch precision are
+\emph{$d=3$ cubic} $A_{\mathrm{fit}} = 5.978 \pm 0.026$ (dps$=800$,
+$50$ families) and \emph{$d=4$ quartic}
+$A_{\mathrm{fit}} = 7.954 \pm 0.0037$ (dps$=1200$, $60$ families),
+both within $1\sigma$ of the V6 prediction $A = 2d$ after the
+standard $1/\log N$ finite-window correction; these numbers are
+inherited from bridge session 068 and reproduced in
+\texttt{M4-V0-CLOSURE-CASCADE-106/m4\_v0\_closure\_statement\_canonical.md}.
+
+\subsection{Item~2 --- M6.CC R1 closure (V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$ on the $D_6 \to D_7$ degeneration boundary, via the Q4 v2 cascade)}
+\label{sec:closure-cascade-m6}
+
+The M6.CC R1 closure landed on the bridge across two sessions: the
+Q4 round-2 substrate-direct derivation packet
+\texttt{T1-OPERATOR-Q4-ROUND2-DIRECT-DERIVATION-PACKET-130}
+(bridge SHA \texttt{10b5cf6}), and the synth verdict-absorption
+session \texttt{T1-SYNTH-Q4-V2-VERDICT-ABSORPTION-131}
+(bridge SHA \texttt{8a22b11}; verdict
+\textsf{GO\_ROUTE\_F\_FIXED\_POINT\_DISTINGUISHED} HIGH conf.).
+The closure mechanism reframes the V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$ stratum as
+sitting on the $D_6 \to D_7$ degeneration boundary of Sakai's
+Painlev\'e III hierarchy: the V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$ image
+$(\eta_\infty, \eta_0, \theta_\infty, \theta_0) = (1/6, 0, 0, -1/2)$
+violates the standing assumption $\eta_0 \neq 0$ of the
+$P_{III}'(D_6)$ generic open stratum, and the surviving Cremona
+symmetry reduces to $\widetilde{W}_a(A_1)$ on the
+$P_{III}'(D_7)$ sector. Substrate anchors:
+Okamoto~\cite{Okamoto1987} \S 1 (Hamiltonian conventions);
+Ohyama, Kawamuko, Sakai, Okamoto~\cite{Ohyama2006} \S 3.1
+(the $D_6 \to D_7$ reduction map and the resulting $D_7$-type
+$P_{III}$ Hamiltonian);
+Kajiwara, Noumi, Yamada~\cite{KNY2017} \S 8.5 (the $E_8^{(1)}$
+discrete Painlev\'e Cremona-action ladder and the
+$\widetilde{W}_a(A_1)$ subgroup);
+Sakai~\cite{Sakai2001} (rational-surfaces / affine-root-systems
+classification underpinning the $D_n^{(1)}$ surface labelling).
+This closure converges with the off-generic-stratum diagnosis of
+the 069r3 final synthesis (bridge SHA \texttt{ae5b7f7},
+\texttt{T1-SYNTH-069R3-FINAL-VERDICT-ABSORPTION-124}): two
+independent T1-Synth threads land on the same structural feature
+(V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$ on the degenerate locus of $P_{III}(D_6)$) from
+different angles. The convergence is recorded as a positive forensic
+signal in \texttt{sessions/2026-05-09/T2-EXECUTOR-115-ROUTE-F-D7-FIXED-POINT-EXTRACTION-132/unexpected\_finds.json}.
+
+\subsection{Item~3 --- Route F slot 115 numerical re-derivation}
+\label{sec:closure-cascade-route-f}
+
+The Route F executor session
+\texttt{T2-EXECUTOR-115-ROUTE-F-D7-FIXED-POINT-EXTRACTION-132}
+(bridge SHA \texttt{8ebd1eb}, 2026-05-09) reproduces the synth
+Q4 v2.0 structural payload at agent-side numerical precision
+$\mathrm{dps} = 300$. Pushing the V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$ image
+$(\eta_\infty, \eta_0, \theta_\infty, \theta_0) = (1/6, 0, 0, -1/2)$
+through the Ohyama--Kawamuko--Sakai--Okamoto~\cite{Ohyama2006}
+\S 3.1 reduction map yields
+$(\alpha, \beta, \gamma, \delta) = (0, 0, 1/9, 0)$ with all
+residuals below $10^{-200}$ and the relation
+$\gamma\delta = 0$ (violating the generic $P_{III}'(D_6)$ standing
+assumption $\gamma\delta \neq 0$, the $D_7$-sector signature). On
+the $P_{III}'(D_7)$ sector the surviving Cremona action is
+$\widetilde{W}_a(A_1)$ with simple reflection
+$s_1: \alpha_1 \mapsto -\alpha_1$; the V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$ image
+sits at $\alpha_1 = 0$, the $s_1$ fixed point, recovered as a
+closed-form mpmath identity. The companion paper PCF-1
+\cite{PCF1} carries the manuscript pull-back: a new labelled
+remark \verb|rem:vquad-d7-s1| in \cite{PCF1} \S V$_{\mathrm{quad}}$
+documents the $D_6 \to D_7$ sector descent and the $s_1$ fixed-point
+identity, with a cross-cascade convergence note pointing to the
+069r3 off-generic-stratum diagnosis (bridge SHA \texttt{ae5b7f7}).
+The numerical re-derivation is reproducible from the script
+\texttt{vquad\_p3d6\_recovery.py::compute\_d6\_to\_d7\_reduction\_at\_v\_quad}
+and is logged as five AEAL claims in
+\texttt{sessions/2026-05-09/T2-EXECUTOR-115-ROUTE-F-D7-FIXED-POINT-EXTRACTION-132/claims.jsonl}.
+
